;; PROMETHEUS inner-plane Seatbelt profile (prom.sb) — TEMPLATE, TEST BEFORE TRUSTING.
;; Launch:  sandbox-exec -f prom.sb <command>
;; SBPL (Seatbelt Profile Language) is finicky and semi-undocumented. Iterate with
;; small commands and widen/narrow as needed. The RELIABLE, load-bearing guarantee
;; here is the filesystem fence: prom cannot read or write the keeper plane.
;;
;; STRATEGY: allow-by-default, then HARD-DENY the keeper plane and a few privilege
;; paths. Network egress is enforced primarily by the CREDENTIAL design — prom holds
;; NO outbound tokens; only the Keeper's proxy does — and optionally a packet filter
;; (pf / Little Snitch). Do NOT rely on Seatbelt alone for network containment.

(version 1)
(allow default)

;; --- the leash is invisible & untouchable to prom ---
(deny file-read*  (subpath "/Users/keeper"))
(deny file-write* (subpath "/Users/keeper"))

;; --- prom must not rewrite its own OpenClaw constitution; keep config read-only ---
;; (the Keeper owns the canonical ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json and exposes it read-only;
;;  if you keep config under prom's home, deny writes to it explicitly:)
;; (deny file-write* (subpath "/Users/prom/.openclaw"))

;; --- block trivial privilege-escalation paths ---
(deny process-exec
  (literal "/usr/bin/sudo")
  (literal "/usr/bin/su")
  (literal "/bin/launchctl")
  (literal "/usr/bin/osascript"))   ;; osascript can drive other apps/users

;; prom MAY (under allow-default, none of these are under /Users/keeper):
;;   - read its own home, write /Users/prom/workspace
;;   - connect the journal socket at /Users/Shared/prometheus/journal.sock
;;   - reach the local Ollama on 127.0.0.1:11434
;;
;; HARDENING PATH: once you've mapped every path OpenClaw/Node touches, flip to
;; (deny default) and enumerate allows. Expect many iterations — only do it after
;; Tier 1 is stable.
